        "subtitle": "From Transistors to AI",
        "version": "v1.5.0",
        "aboutProject": "",
        "description": "It's often a little startling—or maybe even a bit scary—to witness what Artificial Intelligence (AI) is capable of these days. It feels as if the distant future was suddenly delivered right to our doorstep. But when you stop to think about it, this massive shift couldn't have just appeared by magic.\nWho was the first person to come up with such a wild idea? How did that one struggling startup become the Big Tech giant it is today?\nSilicon Age was born out of these simple, underlying curiosities.\nPeople have mixed predictions about AI. Some worry it's 'just another bubble,' while others anticipate 'a seismic transformation that will upend the world.' In this moment of confusion, we believe we need to trace the path technology has taken to find the answers.\nOf course, this story is too immense to organize alone. That's why, from the very beginning of creating this website you are viewing now, we collaborated with smart AI companions. We are using the power of AI to gather the scattered fragments of tech history, finding and documenting the hidden 'connections' within them.\nFrom the birth of the transistor—the 'Stone Age' of semiconductors—to the emergence of cutting-edge generative AI. If you share our curiosity, we believe this journey through time and technology will be quite fascinating.",
